definition: letter/mail/CL:封[feng1]/to trust/to believe/to profess faith in/truthful/confidence/trust/at will/at random

sentences.english: If you do not have a PO Box, use your work address.
sentences.chinese: 如果你沒有郵政信箱，使用你的工作地址。

sentences.english: A post office box number is not acceptable.
P. O. Box will not be accepted.
Now consider your email or postal mailbox.
sentences.chinese: 現在以您的電子郵件或郵政信箱爲例。

sentences.english: What does it cost to rent a post office box?
sentences.chinese: 租用郵政信箱的費用是多少？

sentences.english: The consignee's address is post office or other official departments.
sentences.chinese: 收方地址爲敏感部門或郵政信箱。

sentences.english: P. O. Boxes and overseas addresses are not accepted.
sentences.chinese: 郵政信箱及海外地址恕不接受。

sentences.english: For further details, write to P O Box 179.
sentences.chinese: 要了解更多的細節，請來信寄一七九號郵政信箱。

sentences.english: Do not use a P. O. box or in-care-of address.
sentences.chinese: 不要使用郵政信箱或轉交地址。

sentences.english: Overseas address and P. O. Box are not acceptable.
sentences.chinese: 海外地址及郵政信箱恕不接受。
